    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>diced shallot</strong> to a small bowl with the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>grated garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped parsley</strong></p><p>Add 3 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up - this is your <strong>chimichurri dressing</strong></p><p>Soak your <strong>skewers</strong> in <strong>cold water</strong> (this prevents them from burning whilst cooking)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-3-1654602054069-x200.jpg",
